---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Refund Policy — YKS" description="How refunds work at YKS: instant-access digital products, reviewed fairly on a case-by-case basis." canonical="/refund-policy">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-14">
    <h1 class="text-4xl tracking-tight font-semibold mb-6">Refund Policy</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-invert">
      <p><strong>Refunds are reviewed individually, on a case-by-case basis.</strong></p>

      <p>Our paid guides and packs are digital products with instant access, so we don't offer automatic, no-questions refunds. What we do offer is a fair hearing: if something isn't right, email us and we'll work with you to put it right.</p>

      <p>We'll typically refund or replace when, for example:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>a file is corrupted, won't download, or won't open;</li>
        <li>the product is materially not as described;</li>
        <li>you were charged twice or bought the same item by mistake;</li>
        <li>you bought the wrong item and haven't used it.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Because access is instant and the files are yours to keep, "I changed my mind" or "I already downloaded and used it" generally won't qualify — but we'd still rather hear from you than have you feel stuck. Reach out within a reasonable time (ideally within 30 days of purchase) and tell us what happened.</p>

      <p>Nothing here limits any statutory rights you may have under your local consumer law.</p>

      <p class="text-sm text-text-subtle mt-8">
        Almost everything we make is <a href="/guides" class="text-primary underline underline-offset-4">free</a> — try the free guides and tools first, so a paid purchase is only ever a top-up on something you already know you like.
        Questions or a request? <a href="/contact" class="text-primary underline underline-offset-4">Get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
